Manila Chinatown Dimsum Experience
Dimsum can be translated to mean snack. In this experience we will be trying out iconic dimsum as well as some other snacks beloved by the locals. We'll meet up at the Binondo Church and learn a brief history of the area. Then make our way towards our first stop where we'll be sampling some baked savory filled pastries reminiscent of an empanada. We then make our way to a hole-in-the-wall dumpling place and try out some fresh hand made dumplings. Next, we walk along the main street of Chinatown as we take in the different sights and sounds before making our way to our next stop and try some fluffy meat buns stuffed with sweet and savory pork. Soon after, we'll squeeze our way through the long lines and try out some dimsum classics such as Crystal Shrimp Dumplings and Beancurd Rolls washed down with iced milk tea. We'll continue our walk deeper into Chinatown and try a different kind of bun, filled with a meatball. Then top off our experience with sweet treats from 2 different bakeries. Other things to note Dress light and casual to battle heat/humidity. But keep it modest. Travel towards the meet up point early. Let me know your food restrictions. Not a suitable activity for Vegans or Vegetarians.

No English menu, but don't worry as I will teach you the real Filipino way of ordering food and drinks. A local beer as we eat Then chill at the beautiful 360 rooftop bar in Makati. Photography is included in this experience. Inclusions: - English speaking tour guide, that's me, Venus. - Dinner - Photography When the activity is done I can assist you to find your ride back to your hotel. Reminder: I am flexible with times just let me know if your alone, couple or group so I can plan accordingly, Eat, laugh and explore with me during our Makati Street Food Experience. Other things to note As we will walk around before dinner, please wear comfortable shoes and come hungry. If you have allergies or something you can't eat, please tell me beforehand

Bambike Ecotours Ligtasin Cove
You start out at our Bambike Ecotours meeting point where you sign in and select your bamboo bike for the trip. There will be a short introduction to the Bambike company and a safety briefing before heading out. Once oriented with the bike and the route, you will set off towards Talim Point at the tip of the Luyahan Penninsula. It is about 3.2 kilometers away on paved and dirt roads through the forest. We will spend some time exploring the Talim Point area which is great for taking pictures. And we will have a drink at the local caretaker's shop (soda, water, juice, or beer). On the way back we will take a route that brings us on to a portion of the beach where we can see fishing boats and the coral reef from shore. When you finish up the tour you can enjoy freshly brewed Barako specialty coffee, ice tea, or try out a local craft beer. Total biking distance will be under 7 km.
